
  ✨ Architectural Strengths to Preserve


Decision to use **pure Cypher** instead of Graph Data Science library is **architecturally sound**:

✅ **Portability** - Works on Neo4j Desktop, Aura, Docker, anywhere
✅ **Simplicity** - No extra dependencies, easier deployment
✅ **80/20 Rule** - Pure Cypher gives 80% of GDS value with 20% of complexity
✅ **Maintainability** - One fewer thing to version-match and upgrade

**When to reconsider GDS:**
- You need PageRank for knowledge importance (pure Cypher is O(n²))
- Community detection (Louvain) for learning clusters
- Advanced similarity algorithms (Node Similarity, FastRP)
- Very large graphs (>1M nodes) where GDS performance matters

For now, **stick with pure Cypher** and get more value from your existing patterns first.
